<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_kærkæ-mærkæ" xml:lang="os">
    <form type="lemma">
        <orth>kærkæ-mærkæ</orth>
    </form>
    <sense>
        <sense>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>яркий</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>bright</q>
            </cit>
        </sense>
        <sense>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>пестрый</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>many-coloured</q>
            </cit>
        </sense>
        <sense>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>расцвеченный</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>coloured</q>
            </cit>
        </sense>
    </sense>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Для первой части ср. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
            ><lang/><w>kärk</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w>körk</w><gloss><q>красота</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                ><w>körkü</w><gloss><q>прекрасный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                ><w>kärkäi</w><gloss><q>быть украшенным</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>II 1098, 1259–1261</biblScope></bibl>). Вторая
        часть (%imærkæ%i) представляет не имеющий самостоятельного значения ассонанс к первой, как в
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qūlon-mūlon"/> ‘пестрый’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_kʼæʒ-mæʒ"/> ‘кривой’ и т. п. (<bibl><ref target="#ref_РОСл."
                /><biblScope>611–612</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">For a first part cf. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
            ><lang/><w>kärk</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                ><w>körk</w><gloss><q>beauty</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                ><w>körkü</w><gloss><q>beautiful</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                ><w>kärkäi</w><gloss><q>to be decorated</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>II 1098, 1259–1261</biblScope></bibl>). The second
        part (%imærkæ%i) is a vocalic alliteration of the first part, which has no individual
        meaning, the same way as in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qūlon-mūlon"/> ‘many-coloured’,
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼæʒ-mæʒ"/> ‘crooked’ etc. (<bibl><ref target="#ref_РОСл."
                /><biblScope>611–612</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
</entry>
